Sentencas: PrSrCo(1-x)CuxO(4+delta) (x = 0.0, 0.1, 0.3, 0.5) are synthesized by solid-state reaction method.
Titulo: Tuning the high temperature properties of PrSrCoO4 cathode with Cu2+ dopant for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effects of Cu2+ doping on electrical conductivity, thermal expansion, oxygen diffusion properties and oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) activity are investigated.
Titulo: Tuning the high temperature properties of PrSrCoO4 cathode with Cu2+ dopant for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: PrSrCo1-xCuxO4+delta oxides crystallize in a single-phase tetragonal structure with I4/mmm space group.
Titulo: Tuning the high temperature properties of PrSrCoO4 cathode with Cu2+ dopant for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Partial substitution Co3+ by Cu2+ results the increase of electrical conductivity and decrease of thermal expansion coefficient.
Titulo: Tuning the high temperature properties of PrSrCoO4 cathode with Cu2+ dopant for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Introducing Cu2+ promotes the formation of interstitial oxygen, accelerates the kinetics of oxygen transport, and significantly improves the electrocatalytic activity of ORR.
Titulo: Tuning the high temperature properties of PrSrCoO4 cathode with Cu2+ dopant for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The lowest area specific resistance (ASR) value of 0.08 U cm(2) is obtained for the PrSrCo0.7Cu0.3O4+delta cathode at 700 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Tuning the high temperature properties of PrSrCoO4 cathode with Cu2+ dopant for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The ORR mechanism study demonstrates that Cu-doping (30%) promotes the charge transfer process.
Titulo: Tuning the high temperature properties of PrSrCoO4 cathode with Cu2+ dopant for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The reaction rate control step on PrSrCo0.7Cu0.3O4+delta cathode is the dissociation and surface diffusion process of adsorbed molecular oxygen.
Titulo: Tuning the high temperature properties of PrSrCoO4 cathode with Cu2+ dopant for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
